{
  "id": "019ce53c-8952-7f23-9780-b03ce64f6b57",
  "content": "## Dashboard: Interactive Knowledge Graph — Design Decisions (Agent A)\n\n### Endpoint: GET /api/dashboard/graph/scope\n- Returns `{ nodes: [{id, label}], edges: [{from, relation, to, weight}] }` for the default scope\n- Strategy: reads all entries via `knowledge_files::read_scope()`, then calls `graph.edges()` per entry with `EdgeDirection::Both`, deduplicates by `from:relation:to` key\n- Does NOT modify the `GraphStore` trait (avoids conflict with Agent B)\n- Node labels are content previews (first 80 chars)\n\n### Frontend: Canvas-based force-directed graph (no d3)\n- Custom spring-electric force simulation in Preact with HTML5 Canvas\n- Features: node drag, mouse wheel zoom, click-to-select with detail panel, edge colors by relation type\n- Polls `/api/dashboard/graph/scope` every 10s\n- Falls back to edge table when 0 edges or >500 edges\n- No external dependencies added",
